{{Infobox sport tournament | name = 2006 Basque Pelota World Championships | image = 2006 Basque Pelota World Championships logo.png | caption = Tournament logo | location = {{flagicon|Mexico}} [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]] | start_date = 22 September | end_date = 1 October | administrator = [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]] | tournament_format = | venues = | teams = 18 | purse = | champions = {{flag|Mexico}} | runners-up1 = {{flag|Spain}} | runners-up2 = {{flag|France}} | matches = | points = | attendance = | previous = [[2002 Basque Pelota World Championships|2002]] | next = [[2010 Basque Pelota World Championships|2010]] | website = www.xvcampeonatomundial.com }}
The '''2006 Basque Pelota World Championships''' were the 15th edition of the [[Basque Pelota World Championships]] organized by the [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]].
==Participating nations== {{col-begin|width=70%}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Argentina}} *{{flag|Belgium}} *{{flag|Brasil}} *{{flag|Chile}} *{{flag|Costa Rica}} *{{flag|Cuba}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Dominican Republic}} *{{flag|Ecuador}} *{{flag|France}} *{{flag|Guatemala}} *{{flag|Italy}} *{{flag|Mexico}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Peru}} *{{flag|Philippines}} *{{flag|Spain}} *{{flag|United States}} *{{flag|Uruguay}} *{{flag|Venezuela}} {{col-break}} {{col-end}}
==Events== A total of 14 events were disputed, in 4 playing areas.<ref name="mexico2006">{{cite web| title=Palmares des Championnats du Monde - Mexico 2006| date=2009| language=French| url = http://www.pelota-2010.fr/palmares.php?id=2006| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090827141851/http://www.pelota-2010.fr/palmares.php?id=2006| archive-date = August 2009| accessdate=20 September 2016}}</ref>
