{{Infobox football club | clubname = AS Sud-Est | image = AS Sud-Est.png | image_size = 200 | fullname = Association Sportive Sud-Est | nickname = | founded = {{start date and age|2015|2|28|df=yes}}<ref name="Bordes">{{cite web|url=http://www.lenational.org/las-sud-mise-jeunesse-se-maintenir-d1/ |title=L’AS Sud-Est mise sur la jeunesse pour se maintenir en D1 |editor=Bordes, Gérald |date=17 January 2017 |publisher=Le National |accessdate=3 April 2017}} {{fr}}</ref> | ground = [[Parc Pinchinat de Jacmel]]<ref name="Bordes"/> | coordinates = | capacity = | chairman = | manager = | league = [[Ligue Haïtienne]]<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haiti2016.html RSSSF - Haiti: Championnat National D1 2016]</ref> | season = 2016 | position = Championnat National D2 (promoted) }}
'''Association Sportive Sud-Est''' (or simply '''AS Sud-Est''' or '''ASSE''') is a professional [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Sud-Est (department)|Sud-Est]], [[Haiti]].<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/live-scores/clubs/club=haiti-asse-2000019574/index.html FIFA: ASSE]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://score.fr/haiti-d1-nouvelle-saison-debute-week-end.html |title=Haïti – D1 : La nouvelle saison débute ce week-end! |editor=Vieri, Keke |date=3 March 2017 |publisher=Score.fr |accessdate=19 March 2017}} {{fr}}</ref> The club was the 2016 Division 2 Championship (''Championnat d'Ascension''), and quickly elevated to Division 1 in less than two years since its founding. Former Senator, Senator Edwin (Edo) Zenny is honorary President.<ref name="Bordes"/>
==History== The Association Sportive Sud-Est was founded on 28 February 2015. It won the Division 2 and was promoted to Division 1 after the 2016 season. Its first match in D1 came against [[América des Cayes]], where the match ended in a 1–1 draw. Its first win in the top division came against [[Tempête FC]] on 18 March 2017 ending the match 0–3.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/live-scores/nationalleagues/nationalleague=haiti-premiere-division-2000000153/matches/index.html#month3-2017 FIFA - Matches: March 2017]</ref>
