'''Aigle Noir Athlétic Club''' ({{IPA-fr|ɛɡl nwaʁ}}, [[English language|English]]: ''Black Eagle'') commonly referred to as '''Aigle Noir''', is a professional [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Port-au-Prince]], [[Haiti]], particularly in [[Bel Air, Haiti|Bel Air]].<ref name="Haitifound">[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haitifound.html Haiti – List of Foundation Dates]</ref><ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haitichamp.html RSSSF: Haiti – List of Champions] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304024733/http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haitichamp.html |date=2016-03-04 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://lenouvelliste.com/lenouvelliste/article/59131/57-bougies-pour-lAigle-Noir-Athletic-Club |title=57 bougies pour l'Aigle Noir Athlétic Club |editor=Bellevue, Emmanuel |date=27 June 2008 |publisher=Le Nouvelliste |accessdate=11 April 2016 }} {{fr}}</ref>

==History==
The club was founded on 27 June 1951 as Aigle Noir ''Athlétique'' Club.<ref name="Haitifound"/>

Since, the [[2010 Haiti earthquake]], the club is currently playing in the [[Stade Sylvio Cator]] until their home field, Parc de la Paix,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metropolehaiti.com/metropole/full_spor_fr.php?id=5417 |title=Football: L’Aigle Noir rate l’occasion de creuser l’écart  |editor=Chéry, John |date=14 October 2002 |publisher=Métropole Haiti |accessdate=11 April 2016}}</ref> is rebuilt.<ref>[http://aiglenoirac.com/en/about-our-club/arena/ Aigle Noir Athlétic Club: Parc la Paix – Delmas 2]</ref>

