{{Infobox Stadium | stadium_name = Stadion im. Edwarda Jancarza | nickname = Jancarz | image = [[File:Stadion Stali Gorzow.jpg|250px]] | location = [[Gorzów Wielkopolski]], [[Poland]] | coordinates = {{coord|52|43|15|N|15|13|41|E|region:PL-LB_type:landmark_source:GoogleEarth|display=it}} | broke_ground = | opened = 1951 | renovated = 2007-2011 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Gorzów Wielkopolski City | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | nicknames = | tenants = [[Motorcycle speedway|Speedway team]]: [[Stal Gorzów Wielkopolski]] | seating_capacity = 15,000<ref>http://www.stalgorzow.pl/pl/menu/3/klub.html</ref> | dimensions = }}
'''Edward Jancarz Stadium''' ({{lang-pl|Stadion im. Edwarda Jancarza}}) is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Gorzów Wielkopolski]], [[Poland]]. It is currently used mostly for [[motorcycle speedway|speedway]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Stal Gorzów Wielkopolski]] in the [[Speedway Ekstraliga]]. The stadium has opened in 1951.
It is named after [[Edward Jancarz]], a former speedway rider from Gorzów Wielkopolski who finished third in the [[1968 Individual Speedway World Championship|1968 World Final]] in [[Sweden]], and helped Poland win the [[1969 Speedway World Team Cup]] at home in [[Rybnik]]. Jancarz was murdered by his wife in 1992.
== Hosted == === International === * '''[[Speedway Grand Prix]]:''' [[2011 Speedway Grand Prix of Poland II|2011]], [[2012 Speedway Grand Prix of Poland|2012]], 2013, 2014, [[2015 Speedway Grand Prix of Poland II|2015]] * '''[[Speedway World Cup]]:''' [[2010 Speedway World Cup|2010]] ([[2010 Speedway World Cup Event 1|Event One]]), [[2011 Speedway World Cup|2011]] ([[2011 Speedway World Cup Race-off|Race-off]] and [[2011 Speedway World Cup Final|the Final]]) * '''[[Individual Speedway Junior World Championship]]:''' [[2000 Individual Speedway Junior World Championship|2000 Final]] * '''[[Team Speedway Junior World Championship]]:''' [[2009 Team Speedway Junior World Championship|2009 Final]]
=== Polish Championships === * '''[[Individual Speedway Polish Championship]] Finals:''' [[1970 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1970]], [[1974 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1974]], [[1976 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1976]], [[1977 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1977]], [[1978 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1978]], [[1979 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1979]], [[1984 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1984]], [[1985 Individual Speedway Polish Championship|1985]], * '''[[Polish Pairs Speedway Championship]] Finals:''' [[1982 Polish Pairs Speedway Championship|1982]], [[1992 Polish Pairs Speedway Championship|1992]], [[1998 Polish Pairs Speedway Championship|1998]]
