The '''North Battleford Civic Centre''', locally known simply as the Civic Centre, is a 2,500-seat multi-purpose [[arena]] in [[North Battleford, Saskatchewan]] built in 1962.<ref name="bno">{{cite news |url=http://www.newsoptimist.ca/news/local-news/civic-centre-study-to-be-undertaken-1.1576291 |title=Civic Centre study to be undertaken |last=Foster |first=Jayne |newspaper=[[Battlefords News-Optimist]] |date=January 25, 2014 |accessdate=March 17, 2016}}</ref>  It is home to the [[Battlefords North Stars]] [[ice hockey]] team.<ref name="stars">{{cite web |url=http://www.northstars.ca/page/show/1766800-north-stars-and-barons-history |title=History of the junior hockey in the Battlefords |publisher=Battlefords North Stars Hockey |accessdate=March 17, 2016}}</ref> It is also home to the North Battleford Kinsmen Indoor Rodeo, held annually every April.<ref name="rodeo">{{cite news |url=http://www.newsoptimist.ca/sports/local-sports/let-s-get-ready-to-rodeo-1.1578972 |title=Let's get ready to rodeo |last=Cey |first=Trent |newspaper=Battlefords News-Optimist |date=April 24, 2012 |accessdate=March 17, 2016}}</ref>
