'''Plaza de Toros de Salamanca''', nicknamed '''La Glorieta''' or '''Plaza de Toros de La Glorieta''', is a [[bullring]] in [[Salamanca]], [[Castile and León]], [[Spain]]. It is currently used for [[bull fighting]]. The stadium holds 10,858 people. It was built in 1892 and officially opened on September 11, 1893. It is classical in style and has three levels made of stone, wrought-iron and brick. The ring is {{convert|54|m}} in diameter.


